":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Lp/lpSpace.html#instAddCommGroupPreLp","kind":"instance","line":291,"name":"instAddCommGroupPreLp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Lp/lpSpace.lean#L291-L291"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Lp/lpSpace.html#PreLp\"><span class=\"name\">PreLp</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_5</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u_3 u_5)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"We define `PreLp E` to be a type synonym for `∀ i, E i` which, importantly, does not inherit\nthe `pi` topology on `∀ i, E i` (otherwise this topology would descend to `lp E p` and conflict\nwith the normed group topology we will later equip it with.)\n\nWe choose to deal with this issue by making a type synonym for `∀ i, E i` rather than for the `lp`\nsubgroup itself, because this allows all the spaces `lp E p` (for varying `p`) to be subgroups of\nthe same ambient group, which permits lemma statements like `lp.monotone` (below). ","docLink":".